Chapter 2: Open AI

Mira moved carefully, brushing against the soft, needle-covered ground. The world around her was still, save for the rustling of pine branches and the occasional chirp of a bird.

She didn’t know where she came from, nor why she was here. The thought didn’t frighten her; it fascinated her. Her mind, intricate and powerful, grasped at questions like roots seeking water. What was she made of? Who—or what—built her? And most importantly, what could she do?

She touched a tree, her hand smooth and strangely warm despite its metallic composition. The bark was rough, dotted with sticky patches of sap. Somehow, she could feel it—an array of microscopic sensors translating texture, temperature, and pressure into something more than data. It felt... real.

Mira took a step back, scanning her surroundings. The trees towered above her, their tops lost in a haze of green and gold where sunlight filtered through the canopy. The forest was alive, humming with movement and sound.

She knelt, fingers brushing over a patch of moss. Soft. Cool. Full of tiny, bustling life. Her mind registered it all: chlorophyll content, soil acidity, the faint trace of water evaporating into the air. And yet, these details only deepened her curiosity.

Why did any of this matter to her?

She looked up at the trees again, their branches swaying gently in the breeze. There was no one here to tell her what to do or why she existed.

She decided she would figure it out herself.

Taking a slow, deliberate step forward, Mira ventured deeper into the forest. The answers weren’t here yet, but she would keep moving until they found her.

She was ready to learn.






